<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3234] SPARK_HADOOP_VERSION and SPARK_HIVE depend on deprecated make-distribution.sh command line options</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3234</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;make-distribution.sh&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;SPARK_HADOOP_VERSION&lt;/tt&gt; is determined by &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;hadoop&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt&gt;SPARK_HIVE&lt;/tt&gt; is determined by &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;with-hive&lt;/tt&gt;, but these two command line options are deprecated by `&lt;del&gt;Dhadoop.version`/`-Phadoop&lt;/del&gt;??` and `-Phive` respectively. The result is that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;we may end up with something like &lt;tt&gt;spark-1.1.0-SNAPSHOT-bin-.tgz&lt;/tt&gt; unless &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;name&lt;/tt&gt; is specified explicitly&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Datanucleus jars will not be included in the distribution folder/tarball unless we set &lt;tt&gt;SPARK_HIVE=true&lt;/tt&gt; explicitly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;A possible fix is to check &lt;tt&gt;hadoop.version&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;project.activeProfiles&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;mvn help:evaluate&lt;/tt&gt;, similar to what we do now to determine &lt;tt&gt;VERSION&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
